Getting the Gist of Markdown's Formatting Syntax
------------------------------------------------
    
This page offers a brief overview of what it's like to use Markdown. The
[syntax page] [s] provides complete, detailed documentation for every feature,
but Markdown should be very easy to pick up simply by looking at a few
examples of it in action. The examples on this page are written in a
before/after style, showing example syntax and the HTML output produced by
Markdown.  

   
        

